    "updated_at": "2014-05-26T16:53:23Z",
    "body": "The specific case you've mentioned needs to stay as an `assert` (or return failure), but I believe that the real problem here is that the compiler is invoking these intrinsics with `*u8` instead of `&str`. If the compiler invoked the intrinsics with `&str`, none of the assertion code would be necessary.\n",
