    "created_at": "2014-05-29T16:23:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-05-29T16:23:57Z",
    "body": "I'm all for shaving off what we can, and in general reducing code size. It sounds like the remaining code size is just code in general, so there may not any more low-hanging fruit in terms of code-size. If https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/93 is accepted then the footprint of `secret_show` will likely be reduced to smaller than it is today.\n\nI wouldn't consider this a will-not-fix thing, but we also don't want to compromise too much on the current functionality of libcore. If you find any size-related issues, please definitely feel free to open an issue, I'd love to trim it down to as small as can be!\n",
